WEBVTT

00:03.838 --> 00:05.270
NELSON:
<i> Haw-haw!</i>

00:07.308 --> 00:08.607
D'oh!

00:08.609 --> 00:10.009
(tires screeching)

00:10.011 --> 00:11.510
(grunts)

00:11.512 --> 00:14.580
(gentle lullaby version of
<i> "The Simpsons</i> Theme" playing)

00:28.796 --> 00:31.463
(sucking)

00:31.465 --> 00:34.366
(humming)

00:35.236 --> 00:38.303
(humming)

00:39.573 --> 00:42.141
(humming)

00:43.077 --> 00:45.310
(humming)

00:47.815 --> 00:49.481
(screaming)

00:51.519 --> 00:53.585
♪ ♪

00:58.359 --> 00:59.925
NARRATOR:
<i> It was the biggest scandal</i>

00:59.927 --> 01:03.028
<i> in the history of</i>
<i> Springfield sports.</i>

01:03.030 --> 01:06.498
<i> Never has someone fallen from</i>
<i> such heights to such lows,</i>

01:06.500 --> 01:09.501
<i> except maybe for that</i>
<i> tightrope walker who sneezed.</i>

01:09.503 --> 01:10.669
<i> That was terrible.</i>

01:12.339 --> 01:15.374
This situation is
a disgusting mockery

01:15.376 --> 01:19.011
of a repulsive joke that would
make me sick to my stomach

01:19.013 --> 01:20.212
if there was there was

01:20.214 --> 01:21.680
one good restaurant
in this town,

01:21.682 --> 01:23.182
which there is not!

01:23.184 --> 01:26.018
(stammers)
There is nothing to vomit.

01:26.020 --> 01:29.021
NARRATOR:<i> And all because</i>
<i> of one young man.</i>

01:29.023 --> 01:31.523
Okay, so I shaved points
in basketball.

01:31.525 --> 01:33.859
Just don't make
a big production of it.

01:33.861 --> 01:36.562
NARRATOR:
<i> This is</i> 22 for 30.

01:36.564 --> 01:38.630
(dramatic orchestral music)

01:46.574 --> 01:48.540
My son is a handful.

01:48.542 --> 01:50.309
Can you say that on TV?

01:50.311 --> 01:53.445
No one ever thought he'd work
for gamblers with the mob.

01:53.447 --> 01:56.115
I always thought he'd work for
gamblers with the mob.

01:56.117 --> 01:57.983
In the morning,
we saw the horrors

01:57.985 --> 02:00.252
of the beaches at Iwo Jima.

02:00.254 --> 02:02.121
DIRECTOR: This is
a sports documentary.

02:02.123 --> 02:03.589
I'm getting there!

02:03.591 --> 02:05.457
In my unit, they called me
"Quarterback."

02:05.459 --> 02:08.460
Because when I borrowed
a quarter, I never gave it back.

02:08.462 --> 02:13.465
At the end of the war,
I had a buck 75, and no friends.

02:13.467 --> 02:15.467
(distorted): I remember it
like it was yesterday.

02:15.469 --> 02:17.402
Or maybe the day before that.

02:17.404 --> 02:19.404
It all started with a prank.

02:19.406 --> 02:21.773
Bart had no idea
where it would lead.

02:21.775 --> 02:24.176
This voice is scaring me.

02:24.178 --> 02:25.677
I need Puppy Goo-Goo!

02:27.248 --> 02:29.448
(normal voice):
Safety kiss!

02:29.450 --> 02:31.483
I think I'll be okay.

02:31.485 --> 02:33.519
(distorted):
I love you.

02:33.521 --> 02:34.953
(distorted scream)

02:34.955 --> 02:37.422
Yeah, so here was
the quote, unquote "prank."

02:37.424 --> 02:40.993
<i> Bart sent out a memo telling</i>
<i> everyone to wear white</i>

02:40.995 --> 02:44.429
<i> for some nonsense called</i>
<i> Polar Bear Remembrance Day.</i>

02:44.431 --> 02:46.131
<i> (chuckles) Yes.</i>

02:46.133 --> 02:48.600
<i> Then the little dickens</i>
<i> sent Skin-ner</i>

02:48.602 --> 02:51.136
<i> a different memo</i>
<i> telling him to wear</i>

02:51.138 --> 02:55.140
<i> a floral shirt in honor of</i>
<i> King Kamehameha's birthday.</i>

02:55.142 --> 02:57.676
<i> (stammers)</i>
<i> Had it ended there, fine.</i>

02:57.678 --> 02:59.545
<i> Pleasant conclusion</i>
<i> to a busy week.</i>

02:59.547 --> 03:01.680
<i> But it didn't end there.</i>

03:01.682 --> 03:03.482
Now don't worry,

03:03.484 --> 03:06.518
all the bees want
are flowers.

03:08.155 --> 03:09.521
(bees buzzing)

03:09.523 --> 03:11.156
Willie, kill the bees!

03:11.158 --> 03:13.659
Not till I hear
their side of it.

03:13.661 --> 03:17.529
NARRATOR:<i> Bart received the</i>
<i> longest detention in history.</i>

03:17.531 --> 03:20.532
<i> Bored, he began</i>
<i> to shoot baskets,</i>

03:20.534 --> 03:23.835
<i>a talent that would irrevocably</i>
<i> make his life better.</i>

03:23.837 --> 03:25.904
<i> Then worse, then better,</i>
<i> then the same.</i>

03:25.906 --> 03:28.340
♪ Wish I had a rabbit
in a hat with a bat ♪

03:28.342 --> 03:29.808
♪ And a '64 Impala ♪

03:29.810 --> 03:31.476
♪ I wish I was, like,
six-foot-nine ♪

03:31.478 --> 03:34.313
♪ So I can get with Leoshi,
'cause she don't know me ♪

03:34.315 --> 03:35.647
♪ But, yo, she's really fine ♪

03:35.649 --> 03:37.316
♪ You know I see her
all the time ♪

03:37.318 --> 03:38.684
♪ Everywhere I go,
and even in my dreams ♪

03:38.686 --> 03:40.352
♪ I can scheme up ways
to make her mine ♪

03:40.354 --> 03:41.853
♪ 'Cause I know
she's livin' phat ♪

03:41.855 --> 03:43.555
♪ Her boyfriend's tall
and he plays ball ♪

03:43.557 --> 03:45.424
♪ So how am I gonna
compete with that? ♪

03:45.426 --> 03:48.193
A troubled young man
who was good at basketball.

03:48.195 --> 03:49.695
I'd never heard of such a thing.

03:49.697 --> 03:51.063
Of course, his detention
was commuted,

03:51.065 --> 03:53.065
and he was made
a starter on the team.

03:54.835 --> 03:57.102
That's my son! My son!

03:57.104 --> 03:58.937
Which is, of course,
another version of me!

03:59.873 --> 04:00.906
(crowd cheering)

04:00.908 --> 04:03.675
Him! Me! Us! Me!

04:03.677 --> 04:07.045
NARRATOR:<i> Everywhere Bart went,</i>
<i> he was given star treatment.</i>

04:07.047 --> 04:08.614
<i> At school...</i>

04:11.085 --> 04:12.150
(grunts)

04:15.055 --> 04:16.088
(grunts)

04:16.090 --> 04:18.090
<i> ...at the public pool...</i>

04:18.092 --> 04:19.691
(Bart laughing)

04:19.693 --> 04:20.692
(Bart grunts)

04:20.694 --> 04:22.794
It's really not
that dangerous.

04:22.796 --> 04:25.097
(laughing)

04:25.099 --> 04:26.965
NARRATOR:
<i> ...with local merchants.</i>

04:26.967 --> 04:28.700
Oh, young basketball star,

04:28.702 --> 04:30.469
I have something
special for you.

04:30.471 --> 04:33.538
The new 7,200-ounce Squishy.

04:33.540 --> 04:36.708
NARRATOR:<i> But not everyone was</i>
<i> celebrating the Bart-mitzvah.</i>

04:36.710 --> 04:38.810
I got an assignment:
write an article

04:38.812 --> 04:41.713
on the school's new hero,
Bart Simpson.

04:41.715 --> 04:43.482
(sighs) This is worse than

04:43.484 --> 04:45.984
when we were square-dance
partners in gym.

04:45.986 --> 04:47.586
♪ Grab your partner
nice and slow ♪

04:47.588 --> 04:48.887
♪ Allemande left and ♪

04:48.889 --> 04:51.990
(slows, distorts):
♪ Do-si-doh. ♪

04:51.992 --> 04:54.293
♪ That's the last time
I had work ♪

04:54.295 --> 04:55.994
♪ Now I'm just a homeless jerk ♪

04:55.996 --> 04:57.996
♪ Allemande left
and prance to the right ♪
(cat yowls)

04:57.998 --> 05:00.299
♪ I need a place
to spend the night. ♪

05:00.301 --> 05:02.267
NARRATOR:
<i> Springfield had never won</i>

05:02.269 --> 05:04.569
<i> a championship in any sport.</i>

05:04.571 --> 05:06.638
<i>The only banner on the gym wall</i>

05:06.640 --> 05:08.740
<i> was one that came</i>
<i> with the building.</i>

05:08.742 --> 05:10.909
<i> But now, there was a shot.</i>

05:10.911 --> 05:13.812
I was so proud of Bart,
I did anything I could

05:13.814 --> 05:15.314
to help him practice.

05:15.316 --> 05:16.948
Mm!

05:16.950 --> 05:18.417
But then it happened.

05:18.419 --> 05:19.985
Fame went to Bart's head.

05:19.987 --> 05:23.422
Just once, I'd like to see
science go to his head.

05:23.424 --> 05:26.458
He's got more D's
than Dolly Parton!

05:26.460 --> 05:28.827
I'm not sure what that means,
but please use the joke.

05:28.829 --> 05:31.096
I paid someone 25 bucks for it.

05:31.098 --> 05:32.197
(music playing over earbuds)

05:32.199 --> 05:34.599
Bart Simpson, can ya
please join the team?

05:34.601 --> 05:36.768
Man, I<i> am</i> the team.

05:36.770 --> 05:38.370
Aw, that tears it!

05:38.372 --> 05:39.805
I'm not coaching anymore!

05:39.807 --> 05:41.640
I'm going back to
what I love doing:

05:41.642 --> 05:44.142
drowning gophers.

05:44.144 --> 05:46.778
(whistling)

05:46.780 --> 05:48.714
Ah! What was that for?!

05:48.716 --> 05:50.849
Our new coach will be
parent-volunteer

05:50.851 --> 05:52.851
and Bart owner, Homer Simpson.

05:52.853 --> 05:54.319
(reporters gasp)

05:54.321 --> 05:55.620
Do you know anything
about basketball?

05:55.622 --> 05:56.621
Why the change?

05:56.623 --> 05:58.290
What is your basketball
philosophy?

05:58.292 --> 06:01.360
Shower at home so no one
makes fun of your weenie.

06:01.362 --> 06:03.729
I learned that from
the late great Red Auerbach.

06:03.731 --> 06:05.831
No more questions!

06:05.833 --> 06:07.399
D'oh!

06:07.401 --> 06:09.835
What the hell is that thing
doing in a gym?!

06:09.837 --> 06:11.636
Your new coach, everybody!

06:11.638 --> 06:13.839
Bart got a coach
who would kiss his butt

06:13.841 --> 06:16.641
like one cheek was Kobe
and the other Kareem.

06:16.643 --> 06:19.478
Well, there is no "I" in "team."

06:19.480 --> 06:21.480
There's no "U" in "effort."

06:21.482 --> 06:22.981
There's no "X" in "dog"!

06:22.983 --> 06:25.050
What do Oscar the Grouch's
feet look like?

06:25.052 --> 06:26.318
Nobody knows!

06:26.320 --> 06:29.087
I have a TV for Bart Simpson.

06:29.089 --> 06:31.823
(sighs) Just put it
with the others.

06:31.825 --> 06:33.925
I'm worried he's getting
a little spoiled.

06:33.927 --> 06:36.228
HOMER:
Oh, that's ridiculous.

06:36.230 --> 06:38.063
Excuse me, sir.

06:38.065 --> 06:40.665
Bart says no unauthorized
photography.

06:40.667 --> 06:43.068
Don't look directly at him!

06:43.070 --> 06:45.237
(Taser zapping)

06:45.239 --> 06:47.305
♪ ♪

06:50.511 --> 06:52.110
NARRATOR:
<i> As Bart's showboating veered</i>

06:52.112 --> 06:54.279
<i> ever closer to globetrotting,</i>

06:54.281 --> 06:55.947
<i> the disrespect grew.</i>

06:55.949 --> 06:57.716
Can you clean that
for me, Coach?

06:57.718 --> 06:59.584
And that, and
that, and those,

06:59.586 --> 07:01.720
and that, and that.

07:01.722 --> 07:03.622
What are you looking at?

07:03.624 --> 07:05.791
HOMER:
What the...?!

07:05.793 --> 07:08.260
NARRATOR:<i> But after one</i>
<i> showboat shot too many,</i>

07:08.262 --> 07:12.564
<i> Homer Simpson had something</i>
<i> he'd never had before: enough.</i>

07:12.566 --> 07:16.034
Uh, son, some of the other
parents are complaining.

07:16.036 --> 07:18.036
Apparently, they're attached
to their children,

07:18.038 --> 07:20.205
and they want to see
them touch the ball.

07:20.207 --> 07:22.541
They can touch it
in the team photo.

07:22.543 --> 07:24.643
I'm going to
draw up a play.

07:24.645 --> 07:26.478
One where you pass.

07:26.480 --> 07:29.281
Why don't you pass a physical,
you boozy bag of goo.

07:29.283 --> 07:32.083
Marge is right.
You're getting spoiled!

07:32.085 --> 07:34.786
Before you strangle me, maybe
you should check the scoreboard.

07:37.057 --> 07:38.924
I'm your dad
and your coach.

07:38.926 --> 07:40.926
And because no one else
would, your godfather.

07:40.928 --> 07:42.894
So hit the bench!

07:42.896 --> 07:44.896
NARRATOR:<i> When we return,</i>
<i> the interesting part.</i>

07:50.304 --> 07:51.903
From now on, you're going
to be a team player.

07:51.905 --> 07:53.338
No more important
than anyone.

07:53.340 --> 07:54.639
Except Milhouse.

07:54.641 --> 07:56.675
I'm on the team
'cause it's my ball.

07:56.677 --> 07:59.010
NARRATOR:<i> Certain people</i>
<i> had begun to notice</i>

07:59.012 --> 08:01.346
<i> Bart's unhappiness.</i>

08:01.348 --> 08:05.617
<i> People with</i>
<i> criminal backgrounds.</i>

08:05.619 --> 08:08.587
They had more records
than Dolly Parton.

08:08.589 --> 08:12.157
Man, that is a joke
that keeps on giving.

08:12.159 --> 08:14.292
This is gonna
break my heart, but...

08:14.294 --> 08:15.794
(groans)

08:15.796 --> 08:18.463
Yeah, the kid was ripe
for criminal exploitation.

08:18.465 --> 08:21.032
And in this town,
the other cops are pathetic.

08:21.034 --> 08:23.535
Fat, lazy.
You want to find one?

08:23.537 --> 08:26.771
Just follow the sound
of a milkshake being sucked.

08:29.276 --> 08:32.677
(slurping)

08:32.679 --> 08:34.613
There's no belt that fits me.

08:34.615 --> 08:36.982
I'm wearing police tape
around my waist.

08:36.984 --> 08:40.652
I saw the kid was upset,
so I took him for cannoli.

08:40.654 --> 08:41.987
That's not a crime.

08:41.989 --> 08:43.822
(whispers): You don't
know what a crime is.

08:43.824 --> 08:46.291
Not that I'd know
what a crime is.

08:46.293 --> 08:47.526
(whispers indistinctly)

08:47.528 --> 08:49.561
What's with all
the psst-psst-psst?

08:49.563 --> 08:52.731
Have you sprung a leak,
or do you want to?

08:52.733 --> 08:54.799
(whispers): I don't think
that's advisable to say that.

08:54.801 --> 08:57.669
I've been told
I was just kidding.

08:57.671 --> 09:00.972
Fat Tony, enjoy this-a
cannoli on-a the house.

09:00.974 --> 09:04.476
It's like eating the
bone-a marrow of an angel.

09:04.478 --> 09:06.511
Mwah! Mwah! Mwah!

09:06.513 --> 09:09.481
NARRATOR:<i> They talked about</i>
<i> life and basketball,</i>

09:09.483 --> 09:12.484
<i> a game Fat Tony</i>
<i> had always loved.</i>

09:12.486 --> 09:14.686
Basketball is just like life.

09:14.688 --> 09:18.323
It's filled with a court,
shooting and guards.

09:18.325 --> 09:19.691
(whispers indistinctly)

09:19.693 --> 09:22.661
Basketball is
nothing like life.

09:22.663 --> 09:25.997
NARRATOR:<i> Fat Tony saw</i>
<i> an opening, and he took it.</i>

09:25.999 --> 09:28.066
FAT TONY:

09:31.271 --> 09:32.671
BART:

09:32.673 --> 09:36.107
FAT TONY:

09:36.109 --> 09:37.776
BOTH:

09:37.778 --> 09:39.578
NARRATOR:
<i> And at his next game,</i>

09:39.580 --> 09:41.947
<i> Bart did a very odd thing.</i>

09:41.949 --> 09:44.516
DREDERICK TATUM:
And with Springfield up
by a meager one point,

09:44.518 --> 09:45.617
star guard Bart Simpson

09:45.619 --> 09:47.385
is just dribbling,
he's not shooting,

09:47.387 --> 09:48.720
with two minutes to go.

09:48.722 --> 09:50.789
♪ ♪

09:55.862 --> 09:58.563
I don't know how,
but Homer gained 12 pounds

09:58.565 --> 10:00.098
chewing towels.

10:00.100 --> 10:02.400
I put jelly on 'em.

10:02.402 --> 10:03.635
(whistle blows)

10:03.637 --> 10:06.037
Time expired!

10:06.039 --> 10:08.773
Bart didn't know it,
but he was point shaving.

10:08.775 --> 10:10.875
That's when a player
wins the game,

10:10.877 --> 10:13.211
<i> but makes sure his team</i>
<i> doesn't cover the spread.</i>

10:13.213 --> 10:16.581
The team's happy, the gamblers
are happy, everybody wins.

10:16.583 --> 10:18.617
The only unhappy person
is someone like me,

10:18.619 --> 10:20.452
who has to explain the thing.

10:20.454 --> 10:23.388
Well, at least you'll let me
play my saxophone.

10:23.390 --> 10:24.589
(inhales deeply)

10:24.591 --> 10:26.091
Good thing you cut that song.

10:26.093 --> 10:29.928
Did you know I once took a train
halfway across Cleveland?

10:29.930 --> 10:31.930
NARRATOR:
<i> This is not a video trick.</i>

10:31.932 --> 10:33.632
<i> He really just stopped moving,</i>

10:33.634 --> 10:36.234
<i> but Bart had just</i>
<i> gotten started.</i>

10:36.236 --> 10:37.802
♪ ♪

10:52.419 --> 10:55.587
You could be an accessory
to a crime, you know.

10:55.589 --> 10:57.422
Are you letting
your anger at Dad

10:57.424 --> 10:59.991
make you into a
patsy for the mob?

10:59.993 --> 11:01.926
Hey, Bart Simpson
is nobody's patsy.

11:01.928 --> 11:05.864
Hey, Bart, Fat Tony says to win
by less than six points.

11:05.866 --> 11:08.633
Here's a list of acceptable
point differentials.

11:08.635 --> 11:10.669
It could be five, four, three...

11:10.671 --> 11:12.871
You realize you're
having this conversation

11:12.873 --> 11:14.139
in front of a reporter.

11:14.141 --> 11:15.674
Hey, I don't see no reporter.

11:15.676 --> 11:18.543
I see a little girl with
futile dreams of fitting in.

11:18.545 --> 11:21.646
Gee whiz, you don't
have to be so mean.

11:21.648 --> 11:24.549
That's the business I'm in!
Whoa! Hey!

11:26.953 --> 11:29.020
(calliope music playing)

11:36.530 --> 11:39.330
Shoot! Shoot!
Just like I drew it up!

11:39.332 --> 11:40.832
Okay, here's a shot:

11:40.834 --> 11:43.902
you're not bald, your hair
left out of embarrassment.

11:43.904 --> 11:45.904
Why, you little...!
(choking)

11:45.906 --> 11:47.338
(crowd gasps)

11:47.340 --> 11:48.339
(crowd cheers)

11:48.341 --> 11:50.175
(buzzer blares)

11:50.177 --> 11:53.078
I'll teach you
to win the game!

11:53.080 --> 11:56.347
You stupid buzzer-beating,
clutch-shooting...
Oh, come on, man.

11:56.349 --> 11:58.349
...ice water in your veins...
I'm taking my talents
to Shelbyville.

11:58.351 --> 12:00.251
...here comes
the post-game interview!

12:00.253 --> 12:02.721
You have to give them credit...
This is the first thing
you've done as a coach.

12:02.723 --> 12:04.589
...they played hard!

12:04.591 --> 12:06.658
People are gonna hear
about this, Dad.
I'm so proud of these boys,

12:06.660 --> 12:09.427
and especially our sixth man...
You're still nicer
than Bobby Knight.

12:09.429 --> 12:10.662
...the fans!

12:10.664 --> 12:12.697
All right,
let me hear your side.

12:12.699 --> 12:15.200
Sorry, my side is
exclusive to my charity,

12:15.202 --> 12:16.901
The American Fart
Association.

12:16.903 --> 12:17.836
Why, you little...!

12:17.838 --> 12:19.738
(grunting)

12:21.208 --> 12:23.775
(laughs)

12:23.777 --> 12:25.610
Checkmate.

12:25.612 --> 12:27.345
(laughs)

12:27.347 --> 12:28.747
D'oh!

12:28.749 --> 12:31.616
NARRATOR:<i> But the boy who could</i>
<i> spin a ball with his doodle</i>

12:31.618 --> 12:33.852
<i> was about to learn</i>
<i> a very tough lesson.</i>

12:37.390 --> 12:39.190
BART:

12:39.192 --> 12:41.259
FAT TONY:

12:43.530 --> 12:45.029
BART:

12:45.031 --> 12:48.066
NARRATOR:<i> Fat Tony denied</i>
<i> he'd made any money,</i>

12:48.068 --> 12:51.903
<i> but this FBI footage</i>
<i> suggests otherwise.</i>

12:51.905 --> 12:53.905
I thought I was just
keeping the score down

12:53.907 --> 12:55.073
to get back at my Dad,

12:55.075 --> 12:57.809
but Fat Tony was betting
against us, every game.

12:57.811 --> 12:59.544
I<i> was</i> a patsy.

12:59.546 --> 13:01.079
Ow! She didn't mean that.

13:01.081 --> 13:03.648
D'oh! Ow! Ow!

13:13.059 --> 13:14.325
I was scared, Milhouse scared.

13:14.327 --> 13:17.128
Why do you keep cutting to me?

13:17.130 --> 13:18.830
And then it got worse.

13:18.832 --> 13:20.932
Fat Tony told me
to lose the finals.

13:20.934 --> 13:23.935
Not win by a little,
but lose or else.

13:23.937 --> 13:25.103
"Or else"?

13:25.105 --> 13:27.405
My client does not
speak like that.

13:27.407 --> 13:30.508
Yeah, now drop
the subject, or else.

13:30.510 --> 13:32.977
Edit that out, or else.

13:32.979 --> 13:35.980
I-I'm gonna stop talking...
or else.

13:35.982 --> 13:37.148
Damn it.

13:37.150 --> 13:39.818
NARRATOR:
<i> What did Fat Tony say to Bart?</i>

13:39.820 --> 13:43.354
<i> His capo, Johnny Tightlips,</i>
<i> refused to talk.</i>

13:47.127 --> 13:49.661
Anyone here own a black
Lincoln Continental,

13:49.663 --> 13:51.963
license plate,
"Zero to Say"?

13:51.965 --> 13:53.164
It's being towed.

13:53.166 --> 13:54.465
Sir, you're the
only one here.

13:54.467 --> 13:55.834
I saw you
get out of it.

13:55.836 --> 13:57.368
Yeah, maybe it is.
Maybe I am.

13:57.370 --> 13:58.870
Maybe you did.
Or maybe it's not.

13:58.872 --> 14:00.271
And I'm not, and you didn't.

14:00.273 --> 14:02.040
But you didn't hear this,
that, or the other thing.

14:02.042 --> 14:02.941
Or maybe you did.

14:02.943 --> 14:06.044
Hey! My granny's in there!

14:06.046 --> 14:08.446
Shaving points was one thing,
but he wanted me to lose.

14:08.448 --> 14:11.749
I let down my team.
I let down my town.

14:20.227 --> 14:24.195
So, I guess this is where
I break down and cry.

14:24.197 --> 14:27.732
(crying)

14:27.734 --> 14:29.901
Hey, I'm the one
who's supposed to cry.

14:29.903 --> 14:32.503
No. This is my story.

14:32.505 --> 14:33.504
Tighten on me.

14:33.506 --> 14:34.906
Tighten on me.

14:34.908 --> 14:37.475
Fine. Tighten on him
then rack focus to me.

14:37.477 --> 14:40.044
Dad, this is supposed to be
about us getting together.

14:40.046 --> 14:42.480
Fine. Tighten on him.
Rack focus to me.

14:42.482 --> 14:43.681
Cut to a wide shot.

14:43.683 --> 14:44.716
Split screen with Marge.

14:44.718 --> 14:46.484
Truck in, nice and slow.

14:46.486 --> 14:49.254
<i> Then cut to a "B" roll of me</i>
<i> eating a tuna fish sandwich.</i>

14:49.256 --> 14:51.389
Dad, how did you
learn these things?

14:51.391 --> 14:54.092
Son, show business is
everybody's business.

14:54.094 --> 14:56.928
Dutch angle, photo negative
and freeze!

14:56.930 --> 15:00.164
I'm a excommation point!

15:00.166 --> 15:02.934
In the gym that night, you could
cut the tension with a knife,

15:02.936 --> 15:05.236
but, uh, we don't allow
knives in school,

15:05.238 --> 15:06.704
not even in metaphors.

15:06.706 --> 15:09.207
♪ We got to fight
the powers that be ♪

15:09.209 --> 15:10.842
♪ Fight the power ♪

15:11.778 --> 15:13.678
♪ Fight the power. ♪

15:13.680 --> 15:15.980
(crowd cheering)

15:18.018 --> 15:20.285
ANGER WATKINS:
Another bucket by Bart Simpson!

15:20.287 --> 15:22.587
His sloppy play
is a distant memory,

15:22.589 --> 15:23.888
like Nelson's father.

15:23.890 --> 15:25.590
Yeah, interesting
side note:

15:25.592 --> 15:28.593
Nelson left a ticket for his
father in case he showed up.

15:28.595 --> 15:30.862
And he did show up, but
then he sold the ticket

15:30.864 --> 15:33.364
without seeing Nelson,
and he skipped town again.

15:33.366 --> 15:34.565
You believe that?

15:34.567 --> 15:36.601
Rejected!

15:36.603 --> 15:38.102
Like I've been rejected.

15:38.104 --> 15:39.871
Nothing but net!

15:39.873 --> 15:41.773
Which is what my mom
wears in the strip club.

15:41.775 --> 15:44.742
It was in the third quarter
when the game really got weird,

15:44.744 --> 15:47.011
and I got a low bar for weird.

15:47.948 --> 15:49.113
(grunts)

15:49.115 --> 15:51.616
Bart went to shoot,
and took a hard foul

15:51.618 --> 15:52.984
from his own best friend.

15:52.986 --> 15:54.686
♪ ♪

16:05.632 --> 16:09.934
Let's just say Bart wasn't the
only one Fat Tony had gotten to.

16:09.936 --> 16:12.570
This<i> was</i> my bobblehead.

16:12.572 --> 16:16.908
They got to him, in my bedroom,
where he bobbled.

16:16.910 --> 16:18.843
Hey, let's just say
that bobblehead

16:18.845 --> 16:21.279
won't be attending
no more giveaway days.

16:21.281 --> 16:23.114
You keep shooting
your mouth,

16:23.116 --> 16:26.751
you'll wind up in that building
going up on Third Street.

16:26.753 --> 16:29.687
It's a Third Street address, but
actually you enter on Lincoln.

16:29.689 --> 16:31.823
Yet another
secret revealed!

16:31.825 --> 16:34.459
I'm sorry, Dad.
I was a jerk.

16:34.461 --> 16:36.127
The good thing
about being a kid

16:36.129 --> 16:39.664
is you get to make mistakes so
you don't make them as an adult.

16:39.666 --> 16:40.765
Thanks, Dad.

16:40.767 --> 16:42.667
But don't you still
make mistakes?

16:42.669 --> 16:45.703
The best one
was you, son. Aw.

16:45.705 --> 16:47.472
Now go win that game!

16:47.474 --> 16:49.540
NARRATOR:
<i> And win he did.</i>

16:51.544 --> 16:54.045
He blew our net budget
for the next ten years.

16:54.047 --> 16:56.180
(buzzer blares)

16:56.182 --> 16:58.950
NARRATOR:
<i> But not everyone was cheering.</i>

16:58.952 --> 17:00.184
Is he going for a gun?

17:00.186 --> 17:01.285
(sighs):
Oh.

17:01.287 --> 17:03.154
Get me a gun.
(screams)

17:03.156 --> 17:04.722
We thought we
were goners.

17:04.724 --> 17:07.558
Our lives flashed
before our eyes.

17:07.560 --> 17:09.627
I had a lot of crazy jobs.

17:09.629 --> 17:12.230
And then the cavalry came
on her stupid high horse.

17:12.232 --> 17:13.664
LISA:
Let them go.

17:13.666 --> 17:16.868
Really? And what
do you have on me?

17:16.870 --> 17:17.835
The goods.

17:17.837 --> 17:19.871
The goods?
Oh, that sounds bad.

17:19.873 --> 17:22.573
Fat Tony, may I speak
to you in Italian?

17:22.575 --> 17:24.375
I don't know Italian.

17:24.377 --> 17:25.710
How about Sicilian?

17:25.712 --> 17:26.844
That's a language?

17:26.846 --> 17:28.679
How about I say it
like Porky Pig?

17:28.681 --> 17:29.981
E-ba-dee, e-ba-dee, e-ba-dee,
e-ba-dee, e-ba-dee...

17:29.983 --> 17:31.582
Say what you got to say.

17:31.584 --> 17:34.385
Turns out I'm the hero
of this documentary.

17:34.387 --> 17:36.054
I think that deserves a chyron.

17:37.891 --> 17:40.491
It happens that
Fat Tony had a secret,

17:40.493 --> 17:43.728
a secret I had uncovered
with a little bit of research.

17:43.730 --> 17:46.664
<i> I wondered, if Fat Tony</i>
<i> liked basketball so much,</i>

17:46.666 --> 17:47.899
<i> why didn't he play?</i>

17:47.901 --> 17:49.934
<i> Turns out he had.</i>

17:49.936 --> 17:51.869
<i> For a girls' team.</i>

17:51.871 --> 17:55.206
<i> And if there's one thing a</i>
<i> Mafia boss doesn't want known,</i>

17:55.208 --> 17:57.842
<i> it's that he was</i>
<i>the third-string shooting guard</i>

17:57.844 --> 17:59.911
<i> on the</i>
<i> Springfield Little Debbies.</i>

18:02.015 --> 18:04.182
You keep quiet
about what you know.

18:04.184 --> 18:05.950
All of you keep quiet!

18:05.952 --> 18:07.385
Keep quiet about what, boss?

18:07.387 --> 18:08.853
The man Spanx you wear?

18:08.855 --> 18:11.089
Your high school nickname,
Robert DeZero?

18:11.091 --> 18:13.357
The way you cried
at<i> Toy Story 2?</i>

18:13.359 --> 18:14.892
That's not even the sad one.

18:14.894 --> 18:15.960
What? What?

18:15.962 --> 18:18.196
Why do you keep talking?

18:18.198 --> 18:20.031
I'm sorry.
It's a nervous condition.

18:20.033 --> 18:23.634
Can you give me the name of
that secret shrink you see?

18:23.636 --> 18:24.802
So, we made a deal.

18:24.804 --> 18:27.438
I'd forget if Fat Tony forgave.

18:27.440 --> 18:29.240
But now the
secret's out.

18:29.242 --> 18:30.808
It's in a documentary.

18:30.810 --> 18:33.444
No one watches those,
unless it's a documentary

18:33.446 --> 18:36.247
where a rich guy kills people
and no one knows about it.

18:36.249 --> 18:38.282
As far as you know.
(chuckles)

18:41.554 --> 18:43.454
BURNS:
I'm guilty, guilty, guilty.

18:43.456 --> 18:45.056
SMITHERS:
Sir, you know you're on mic.

18:45.058 --> 18:46.991
BURNS: Who is this Mike
you're speaking of?

18:46.993 --> 18:48.159
We'll kill him, too!

18:48.161 --> 18:51.329
NARRATOR:<i> But all sports stories</i>
<i> have an upside,</i>

18:51.331 --> 18:53.998
<i> unless you're</i>
<i> a Detroit Lions fan.</i>

18:54.000 --> 18:57.568
So this young man,
showboat and friend of the mob,

18:57.570 --> 19:00.171
gets off with not even
a slap on the wrist.

19:00.173 --> 19:03.307
It's a travesty
wrapped in outrage,

19:03.309 --> 19:07.145
marinated in a sauce
of everything's gone to hell!

19:08.748 --> 19:10.114
I admit, it was fun.

19:10.116 --> 19:13.484
For a short time, we had
our own little superstar.

19:13.486 --> 19:15.086
And he kept playing.

19:15.088 --> 19:17.455
Then he ran up
against one tall kid,

19:17.457 --> 19:19.757
<i> and found out</i>
<i> he really wasn't that good.</i>

19:19.759 --> 19:23.528
But Lisa, Lisa had a real
talent for journalism.

19:23.530 --> 19:25.096
Whatever that gets us.

19:25.098 --> 19:27.765
Homer, we have to end
on something sweet.

19:27.767 --> 19:29.700
(lovingly):
Whatever that gets us.

19:35.008 --> 19:36.941
♪ Now basketball
is my favorite sport ♪
♪<i> Uh-huh</i> ♪

19:36.943 --> 19:39.110
♪ I like the way they dribble
up and down the court ♪
(whistle blows)

19:39.112 --> 19:41.112
♪ I keep it so fresh
on the microphone ♪

19:41.114 --> 19:42.880
♪ I like no interruption
when the game is on ♪
♪<i> Game's on</i> ♪

19:42.882 --> 19:45.016
♪ I like slam dunks
that take me to the hoop ♪
♪<i> Yeah</i> ♪

19:45.018 --> 19:46.117
♪ My favorite play is... ♪

19:46.119 --> 19:47.485
Sorry, y'all.

19:47.487 --> 19:49.554
♪ I like the pick-and-roll,
I like the give-and-go ♪

19:49.556 --> 19:52.356
♪ And it's basketball,
Bow Wow, let's go... ♪

19:52.358 --> 19:54.959
Yeah. Nothing but nerd.

19:54.961 --> 19:56.227
♪<i> All around the world</i> ♪

19:56.229 --> 19:59.530
♪ We love that basketball ♪
♪<i> Yeah...</i> ♪

19:59.532 --> 20:01.799
No, I didn't!

20:01.801 --> 20:03.968
♪ Basketball... ♪

20:03.970 --> 20:06.904
I admit it, I was a total boob.

20:06.906 --> 20:09.507
Oh! Why do I keep going there?

20:09.509 --> 20:12.476
♪ Let's go ♪
♪ They're playing basketball ♪

20:12.478 --> 20:13.878
♪<i> All around the world</i> ♪

20:13.880 --> 20:15.846
♪ We love that basketball... ♪

20:15.848 --> 20:18.649
NARRATOR:
<i> And Nelson's dad came back.</i>

20:18.651 --> 20:19.917
And I should know.

20:19.919 --> 20:21.052
He's me.

20:21.054 --> 20:23.054
Haw-haw!

20:23.056 --> 20:24.922
(gasps) Papa!

20:24.924 --> 20:28.092
(crying)

20:28.094 --> 20:30.661
So, you're making
narrator money.

20:30.663 --> 20:34.031
That's right, and I
brought Nelson a gift.

20:34.033 --> 20:36.400
Sleeves for my vest!

20:36.402 --> 20:39.837
Son, you look just like
a parole officer.

20:39.839 --> 20:43.040
NARRATOR:<i> And so we were</i>
<i> a family again,</i>

20:43.042 --> 20:45.109
<i> just long enough</i>
<i> to take this picture.</i>

20:55.722 --> 20:58.789
